  <data name="DisclaimerText1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Welcome to The Martian Game!&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  We are a group of researchers exploring question asking. By participating in
  The Martian Game, you consent to the collection and use of your gameplay data —
  such as the questions you ask and your responses — for research purposes.
  Your data will be anonymized, aggregated with other participants' data and
  securely stored to protect its confidentiality.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  Thank you for your participation, and we hope you enjoy the game!&lt;br/&gt;</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DisclaimerText2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Welcome to the Martian City Design Challenge!&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  Your mission is to design a reliable and sustainable energy system for a city on Mars.&lt;br/&gt;To achieve this, you will interact with Mark,
  an AI-powered agent who has the answers to all questions relevant to planning the energy system. Ask creative, analytical, and relevant questions,
  and Mark will provide the information you need. You will earn points based on the quality of your questions, with relevance multiplying your score.&lt;br/&gt;</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DisclaimerText3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The game consists of two parts:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;

  1. Ask Questions: Gather information by asking the agent as many questions as you like.  After each question, you'll
  receive feedback and earn points based on the quality and relevance of your inquiry. During the question phase, a short summary
  of each question you ask will appear on the right side of the screen. When you are ready to plan the energy system,
  click ""Finish Asking"" to proceed to the next phase.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;

  2. Plan Your Energy System: Use the knowledge you've gained to design your energy system within the provided space.
  Once you submit your plan, you'll receive a final score based on your questions, strategy, and overall system design.

  The relevance of your questions will multiply your score.&lt;br/&gt;</value>
  </data>
